Implement strict binding checks for BindAdapter IP configurations  Implemented strict binding checks for IPv4 and IPv6, ensuring that only explicitly configured IP addresses can be used. This behavior can be disabled globally with `StrictBindIP=n` or per-process with `StrictBindIP=[<program>,]=n`.

Add BLOB handling for HOSTENT in DNS filtering for legacy APIs  Implemented support for serialized (BLOB) HOSTENT structures in DNS filtering. This maintains compatibility with legacy name-resolution APIs such as gethostbyname, as well as older applications depending on their behavior.
